claim: Subhas Chandra Bose was never a hero in India.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Subhas Chandra Bose  (  23 January 1897 -- 18 August 1945  )  was an Indian nationalist whose defiant patriotism made him a hero in India , but whose attempt during World War II to rid India of British rule with the help of Nazi Germany and Imperial Japan left a troubled legacy .
